title: Nearly 60 pound pavement in 'Monkey Butt' 5K
text:
Nearly 60 pound pavement in 'Monkey Butt' 5K Event keeps memory of Laken Harrington alive By Staff | Oct 06, 2015 Photo by: Holly Vanorse Spicer Runners and walkers take off during the second annual “Monkey Butt” Memorial 5-kilometer road race Oct. 4 in Warren. View More... 
Warren — The second annual “Monkey Butt” Memorial 5-kilometer road race brought together nearly 60 runners/walkers not just for a 3.1-mile jaunt on Sunday, Oct. 4, but also to keep alive the memory of a friend to many in the community. 
The race, which promotes suicide awareness and prevention, was won by Warren resident Chris Shelmerdine, who crossed the course in 20 minutes and 42 seconds. 
Talia Willis, 14, of Warren was the first female finisher. 
Click for photos from this event. 
Proceeds raised from the event go to the Laken Harrington Memorial Fund, which helps provide children in the community with sport-related equipment, camps and other things. 
In the past year the fund has contributed to basketball camps, soccer cleats, cheerleading shoes, tennis skirts and wrestling camp.
